        <!-- help page content -->
        
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-l">Do I need access to services to use DfE Sign-in?</h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            No. You only need access to an organisation to use DfE Sign-in.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            That means you can, if given approver status, manage users at your organisation without having services on your account.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            However, if you are an end user, you won't be able to do much more than update your details. 
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            <a class="govuk-link-bold" href="/approvers/what-is-approver">More about approvers</a>
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            <a class="govuk-link-bold" href="/end-users/what-is-end-user">More abour end users</a>
        </p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">I’m having trouble adding a service to my account</h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            If you’re an end user (a standard user with no special permissions), please see our 
            <a class="govuk-link-bold" href="/services/request-access">guide to requesting a service</a>.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            If you’re an approver (a user able to manage others), please see our 
            <a class="govuk-link-bold" href="/services/how-to-add">guide to adding a service to your account</a>.
        </p>

        <p class="govuk-body end-of-section">
            Updated April 2021
        </p>

